        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I used the level 53 pet about a dozen times in total before deciding that it is just not worth the mana.</P><P>I tested it reasonably thouroughly before deciding the pet is a real joke and not worth the pp to buy or the time to get yourself. Why?</P><P>Well fear kiting giants at the HG fort in BW with the rogue pet I measured it's damage output compared to the 49 and the difference is marginal - fact is the 53 just does not backstab enough.</P><P>As for when fear breaks - well this is the real reason I trashed the 53 pet. A forest giant ancient kills this pet faster than a fizzle and an invoke fear.</P><P>As for the 56 pet, it is much better than the 53 and the 49. End of story.</P><P>Bottom line. IMHO don't waste your time with the 53 pet at all the 49 is good enough to keep you going till you get Servant of Bones at 56.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
