        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=38273&amp;TOPIC_ID=4823&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Been+away%2E%2Eneed+a+question+answered&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         They have made pets nearly immune to ripotse from critters, which is a big benifit when fear kiting. Previously, it was hard at times to keep the rogue pet alive when fear kiting simply from ripotses, never mind missing a fear/dark. I do not have my numbers infront of me, but this is what I remember about the various pets (max summon, without the Hate Encyclopedia):</P><P>-49 pet (warrior) 2400HP, max hit 55, dual wield, double attack, kick, bash and lifetap.<BR>-53 pet (rogue) 1400HP, max hit 57, dual wield, double attack,  backstab for 150 and lifetap.<BR>-56 pet (monk) 1800HP, max hit 59, dual wield, double attack, flying kick for 71, seems to have a noticably higher AC and ATK then the other pets and lifetap.<BR>-59 pet (warrior) 2400HP, immune to fear, and I will not comment further on it as I do not have this spell yet and have not had a chance to experiment.</P><P>When fear kiting, the 53 pet does get marginally higher DPS then the 49 pet, and seems to be about the same, or even slightly less then the monk pet. If you get more then one resist on a fear refresh, the 53 pet is pretty much toast. Most every necro opts for the 56 pet for most situations once they get a copy, and few ever use the 53 pet again. About the only reason to really use the 49 pet over the 56 pet might be in a situation where spell disruption means more then damage output. Critters will still get spells off, but noticably less frequently.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
